article.headline: Thomas leads Lady Bulldogs with 22 points
article.linkText: Mississippi State cruises to rout of Kentucky
article.story:
STARKVILLE, Miss. (AP) -- LaToya Thomas scored 22 points as (No.
14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) Mississippi State beat Kentucky 96-46 Sunday.

	   Mississippi State (18-6, 6-4 Southeastern Conference) never
trailed in the game. Three other Lady Bulldogs scored in double
figures, including Tan White with 19 points, Rebecca Kates with 11
and Seneca Anderson with 10.

	   Danyelle Payne scored 12 points for Kentucky (9-13, 2-8 SEC).

	   Mississippi State dominated every part of the game, shooting 59
percent from the floor compared to Kentucky's 37 percent.
Mississippi State also outrebounded Kentucky 42-23.

	   Mississippi State also had 20 assists. The Lady Bulldogs led
36-17 at halftime.
